products.title: Silver Oak Cafe Blend 75g
products.body_html: If our baristas have brewed you an espresso-based drink at any of our coffee shops, you’ll be familiar with this special offering since it’s our signature house blend! Our Silver Oak Cafe blend features a combination of Ground coffee beans, processed using either the washed or the unwashed method, to create and has a balanced profile that works well in espresso-based drinks as well as in manual brews such as AeroPress, Pour Over or in cold brews. This versatile medium roast is named after the Silver Oak trees commonly found across coffee plantations in Southern India. This offering is a small way of bringing our cafe experience to you.

products.title: Kolli Berri Estate
products.body_html:
Our first coffee from Harvest ‘24 is a medium-dark roast with chocolatey and nutty flavours. This single-origin ground coffee hails from the beautiful Kolli Berri Estate, set in Chikmagalur, Karnataka. 

While brewing this one, you’ll notice the unique characteristics of the coffee beans, starting with the aroma of dried fruits, followed by a syrupy mouthfeel in every sip. With medium acidity and medium- high bitterness, it offers a full-bodied profile which is enhanced when brewed as an espresso or using an AeroPress, Moka Pot or a French Press.

products.title: Riverdale Estate - Gesha Natural
products.body_html:
A decade ago, Prakashan from Riverdale Estate planted Gesha, one of the world’s rarest coffee varietals, on his farm in Yercaud. In 2023, after eight years of care, came Riverdale’s first Gesha harvest—one that we roasted as part of our debut Nano-X lineup. Since then, this rare varietal has become a core part of our Nano-X, a limited-edition series featuring experimental lots, crafted by a handful of producers and creative Blue Tokai roasters. 

This year’s produce, as Prakashan puts it, is the best so far. The plants have matured and come into their own. The processing has become more and more refined over harvests. And thanks to Subham’s seasoned hands, the same goes for our roasting. 

The lot we sourced was processed using the carbonic maceration method. Ripe, high-density cherries were placed in purpose-built drums. Using special valves, the drums were made oxygen-free and CO2 rich. This controlled fermentation pushed the Gesha’s already exceptional character and complexity further. Slow, controlled drying helped lock in these developments. 

Given the high density of the beans and their delicate aromatics, this Gesha was a worthy challenge for Subham. Drawing on both experience and a bit of experimentation, he added airflow during the development phase of roasting by opening the hopper chute. This reduced the heavy caramelisation that usually builds at this stage, creating an air-roaster-like profile and unlocking striking clarity in the cup. 

We’re excited to present the result: an exceptional nano lot that opens with the aroma of sun melon and orange blossom. A bright and silky mouthfeel reveals layered notes of canary melon, cherries, jasmine, and wild berries. Finishing each sip is an aftertaste of cranberries, adding yet another layer of delightful complexity to your experience. 

We recommend this coffee black, brewed as a Pour Over, or using an AeroPress.

Recommended Resting Period: 6 Days

Note: This coffee pack is a special release with limited availability and, therefore, cannot be included in a subscription plan.

products.title: Riverdale Estate N72
products.body_html:
A favourite in our seasonal line-up since 2020, Riverdale Estate - N72 is back! This fruit-forward medium roast is processed using the natural method, with whole coffee cherries dried intact and fermented for 72 hours. 

Roasted just past first crack by Sunil on our team, it’s a profile designed to highlight the coffee’s vivid character. You'll first notice an aroma of berries and citrus. Next, a bright, syrupy mouthfeel unfolds into layered notes of pineapple, grapefruit, and dried fig. The aftertaste, zesty and refreshing, rounds off each sip.  

We recommend brewing this coffee black, as a Pour Over, or using the AeroPress, to enjoy the full range of flavours this medium roast has to offer.

Recommended Resting Period: 15 Days

products.title: Baarbara Estate
products.body_html:
Coffee beans from Baarbara Estate, roasted medium-dark, have a wonderful aroma of sweet caramel and dried apricot. We love this coffee’s intense, chocolatey flavour profile. To taste the syrupy, smooth mouthfeel of this coffee, we recommend brewing it as a Pour Over, an Espresso or using an AeroPress, Moka Pot or a French Press. If you’ve enjoyed our coffees from Attikan Estate and Sandalwood Estate, you’ll appreciate the sweet aftertaste and medium acidity of this heavy bodied coffee. 

Recommended Resting Period: 8 Days

products.title: Warsanlyngdoh Coffee Collective
products.body_html:
It's always exciting for us to partner with a new farm. With Meghalaya's Warsanlyngdoh Coffee Collective, that excitement runs even deeper. A completely new coffee growing region for us, it speaks of the possibilities that the North East Indian soil holds for specialty production. The collective’s origin goes back a decade, when Daman, a first-generation coffee producer, visited Nongryniang—a remote village in Khasi Hills and home to the nanny who cared for him in his early years. 

"There, nestled among the misty hills, I came across two old coffee plants growing in someone’s backyard. I later learned that back in the 1980s, the government had briefly launched a coffee planting program in the area. Like many such initiatives, it had long been abandoned and forgotten. But those plants stayed with me. And so did the people.", he recounts. Since then, Daman started a decade-long pursuit of craft and community. From shading systems to post-harvest processing, he spent years learning all it takes to grow high-quality coffee. Over time, the collective has grown in both, resolve and numbers, with 75 farmers now contributing to a harvest. They pick only the ripest cherries by hand, which are sun-dried for 15–22 days depending on weather conditions.  

The first coffee that we’ve sourced from the collective is a natural lot we’ve chosen to roast to a medium profile. It brews cups that open with the aroma of raisins, unfolding into a creamy mouthfeel. Notes of blueberry, black tea, and khasi mandarin carry through in each sip, with a long, marmalade-like finish. A balanced coffee, it lends well to various brewing methods, including espresso, Moka Pot, French Press, and AeroPress. It is enjoyable on its own as well as in milk-based beverages.

Recommended Resting Period: 13 Days

products.title: Kuttinkhan Upper Estate
products.body_html:
Our first release from Kuttinkhan Upper Estate, a part of the Kelachandra Group and a Rainforest Alliance certified farm, is here!

A natural lot, this coffee was processed by fermenting whole cherries in an oxygen-free environment, then slow-dried under controlled conditions. Roasted to a medium profile, it crafts vibrant cups with a pleasant acidity and sweetness.

The brew opens with the aroma of red grapes, hinting at the flavour to follow. Soon after, you'll notice notes of red grapes, sweet lime, and cane sugar, wrapped in a syrupy and sweet mouthfeel. Concluding each sip is a chocolatey finish, adding depth to the cup.

Our roasters recommend brewing this coffee as an espresso, AeroPress, French Press and Moka Pot. It tastes great black, and also pairs well with milk.

Recommended Resting Period: 10 Days

products.title: Mooleh Manay Estate – CM Natural
products.body_html:
Returning to our Producer Series after 2023, Komal Sable and Akshay Dashrath share their first experiment with carbonic maceration. Building on the clarity and consistency they achieved with anaerobic fermentation last season, the fifth-generation producers modified their drums to create a CO₂-rich, oxygen-free environment that allows for slower, more controlled fermentation within whole cherries. 

The process began by removing floaters to select only ripe, dense cherries, followed by a brief pre-drying phase to reduce surface moisture. The cherries were then sealed in drums, and a custom culture was introduced to extend the fermentation. Over 60 hours, this combination of carbonic maceration and yeast inoculation ensured thorough mucilage breakdown and the development of deep complexity. 

Post-fermentation, the cherries were dried on raised beds inside a polyhouse. Continuous raking over 7 to 10 days ensured even drying until a final moisture level of 11–12% was reached. 

Roasted light by Rishab from our team, this coffee offers a well-structured cup with notes of fermented red fruit and a bright, juicy sweetness. It opens with the aroma of mixed berries and carries a syrupy mouthfeel, with layered flavours of dried fig, plum, black grape, and mulberry. A chocolatey aftertaste marks the finish, adding further depth. 

We recommend brewing this expressive coffee black, as a Pour Over, or using an AeroPress.

Recommended Resting Period: 16 Days

Note: This coffee pack is a special release with limited availability and, therefore, cannot be included in subscription.

products.title: Amaltas Blend
products.body_html:
An ode to the vibrant burst of yellow that marks the beginning of Indian summers, this blend is our go-to choice for crafting a refreshing batch of coffee including cold brews. In fact, this was originally called the Cold Bold Blend but owing to its diversity (its flavours shine through in a Pour Over or Aeropress), we decided to rename it after one of our favourite neighbourhood trees. 

A blend of washed and natural processed coffees, we’ve roasted it light to accentuate fruity and refreshing citrus notes. The result? Balanced cups with notes of blueberry and milk chocolate, with each sip concluding with a chocolatey finish.  

This light and fruity favourite is best enjoyed black.

products.title: Seethargundu Estate
products.body_html:
We’re so excited to launch our first coffee from Harvest ’25! This light roast is from Seethargundu Estate, one of the few Demeter-certified farms in the country. The estate follows biodynamic practices that treat the farm as a living ecosystem, nurturing soil health, biodiversity, and long-term balance. 

This washed coffee is clean, fruity and tea-like. It opens with the aroma of brown sugar, leading to a syrupy body with notes of sweet lime, apricot, and black tea. The finish carries that tea-like clarity through to the last sip. 

Best brewed as a Pour Over or using the AeroPress, we recommend drinking this coffee black. 

Recommended Resting Period: 18 Days

products.title: Kalledevarapura Estate - Pulp Sun Dried
products.body_html: Our all-time favourite pulp sun-dried coffee from Kalledevarapura Estate is back! This year’s harvest of Coffee beans boasts a medium body and a sweet mouthfeel, perfect for brewing as an espresso, a pour-over, with a Moka Pot, or an AeroPress. Enjoy the rich notes of brown sugar, roasted almond, and raisin—an ideal way to start your day!

products.title: M.S. Estate
products.body_html:
We’re excited to bring you the latest harvest from MS Estate, a cherished part of our perennial selection. This washed coffee features S795 and a rare Ethiopian varietal, with MS Estate being the only Indian farm still cultivating the latter since it was first distributed by the Coffee Board in the late 1990s. 

When you first taste this medium roast, you’ll notice its unique depth and complexity. The aroma of dried fruits, with hints of apricots and peaches, sets the stage for each sip. As you continue, savour the combination of a chocolatey essence along with a distinct tea-like finish that lingers on the palate. 

A versatile coffee, it tastes great black as well as with milk. We recommend brewing it as an espresso, a Pour Over, or using an AeroPress or a Moka Pot.

Recommended Resting Period: 8 Days

products.title: Silver Oak Cafe Blend
products.body_html: If our baristas have brewed you an espresso-based drink at any of our coffee shops, you’ll be familiar with this special offering since it’s our signature house blend! Our Silver Oak Cafe blend features a combination of Ground coffee beans, processed using either the washed or the unwashed method, to create and has a balanced profile that works well in espresso-based drinks as well as in manual brews such as AeroPress, Pour Over or in cold brews. This versatile medium roast is named after the Silver Oak trees commonly found across coffee plantations in Southern India. This offering is a small way of bringing our cafe experience to you.

products.title: Cold Brew Blend Bold
products.body_html: Our Bold Cold Brew Blend, Arabica coffee beans that are roasted medium-dark, brews a full- bodied glass of refreshing cold brew. With notes of dark chocolate, toffee, and roasted nuts, this blend has very little acidity and a bittersweet finish.

products.title: Monsoon Malabar AA- Hoysala Estate
products.body_html:
We’re excited to bring back Monsoon Malabar from Hoysala Estate. The unique flavour profile of this coffee develops when winds and humidity from seasonal monsoon rain change the characteristics of the coffee beans. While this process has its accidental roots in colonial India when a shipment to Europe was attacked by the full force of monsoon winds, similar conditions have been recreated in a controlled environment for consistency in every lot produced. 

When roasted medium dark, the result is a medium-bodied cup that invites with sweet aromas of butter biscuits, treating you to notes of cocoa nibs and dried fruit, concluding with the aftertaste of dark chocolate. Best enjoyed when brewed as an espresso, in the Moka Pot or the French press, the nutty flavour profile of this coffee makes for a delicious cup, either milky or black. 

Recommended Resting Period: 15 Days

products.title: Sandalwood Estate
products.body_html: This perennial coffee from 2023's harvest, Sandalwood Estate, is delicious with tasting notes of rich dark chocolate, sweet prune and zesty orange marmalade. This washed coffee, with coffee beans of the Sarchimor variety, was grown at a lush coffee estate in Coorg. If you’ve tried our coffees from Attikan and Baarbara Estates, you’ll love the chocolatey flavour profile of this medium-dark roast. This heavy bodied coffee has a smooth, syrupy mouthfeel which can best be enjoyed when brewed as an Espresso, pour over or using an AeroPress, Moka Pot or French Press. The long, sweet aftertaste of butter biscuits and dried fruit come through beautifully when you allow the brew to cool down a little.

products.title: St. Joseph Estate
products.body_html:
Meet the first coffee from our newest partner farm, run by a community of Jesuit priests whose stewardship of the land spans generations. 

A washed coffee roasted medium-dark, it opens with warm brown spice aromatics. Each sip carries a syrupy mouthfeel and reminds of grapefruit, roasted almond, and toffee. Its medium-high body gives the cup a comforting depth, complemented by a chocolatey aftertaste. 

Our roasters recommend brewing it as an espresso, or using an AeroPress, Moka Pot, or French Press. A versatile brew, it pairs well with milk, and holds its own black.

Recommended Resting Period: 10 Days

products.title: Attikan Estate
products.body_html:
Attikan Estate's arabica coffee beans come from the Biligiriranga Hills in Karnataka and is make for one of our most popular coffees. Sweet with fruity overtones and balanced acidity, this is the darkest of our standard medium roasts and recommended for espresso lovers. It is a versatile coffee that also works for manual brewing such as Moka Pot, South Indian Filter and AeroPress. 

Located to the south of Mysore, the Biligiriranga Hills, or ‘white hills’ are named after the mist that hangs over the region. At 1650 meters, it is amongst the highest coffee growing regions in India and grows Selection 9, Selection 795, Cauvery and Kent varieties of Arabica, along with Silver Oaks, citrus, and fig trees.

products.title: Krishnagiri Estate
products.body_html:
A single origin dark roast, this coffee comes from a Rainforest Alliance Certified farm. The producers used a custom-designed pulper to process this washed lot, minimising water usage.  

In the cup, you'll first notice the aroma of brown spices. The brew, characterised by mellow acidity, a heavy body, and a velvety mouthfeel, reminds of oak, toasted walnuts, and malt. A bittersweet finish lingers between sips.  

We recommend brewing this coffee as an espresso, using a Moka Pot, French Press, or an AeroPress. It is rich enough to enjoy black, and also pairs well with milk.

Recommended Resting Period: 7 Days

products.title: Basankhan Estate
products.body_html:
We are thrilled to present our first ever single origin dark roast, with coffee beans sourced from a new partner farm— Estate in Chikmagalur, Karnataka. 

This coffee has a journey of rich, complex flavours that will leave you craving for more. As you take a sip, enjoy the velvety mouthfeel reminiscent of dark chocolate, which enhances the overall richness of this brew. The coffee’s body is heavy and round, creating a luscious and full-bodied experience that envelops your palate. If you’ve liked our dark roasts like Vienna and Dhak, you’ll love this one! 
The Basankhan Estate is a family-owned farm located in Chikmagalur, Karnataka with a rich history spanning over 100 years. In addition to coffee, the estate cultivates other crops such as black pepper, oranges, cardamom, lemons, and bananas.

products.title: French Roast
products.body_html:
Our darkest roasted coffee, the French Roast is a blend best enjoyed black for those who like their coffee bold, like a traditional espresso with bittersweet notes. If you’re looking to add milk and still retain a definite bite, this is a great choice.

We recommend brewing this as an Espresso or using manual brewing equipment such as French Press or Manual Grinder.

products.title: Vienna Roast
products.body_html:
The second darkest of our roasts, this blend, with coffee beans from Karnataka and Tamil Nadu, has great body, low acidity, and is a favourite choice for coffee drinkers who enjoy a strong cup, with the characteristic bittersweet notes. The Vienna Roast is best enjoyed with milk. 

We recommend brewing this as an espresso or using manual brewing equipment such as Moka Pot, French Press, or South Indian filter.

products.title: Dhak Blend
products.body_html:
Our Dhak Blend is an ode to one of our favorite Indian trees with its colorful flame-like flowers that signal the onset of Spring. The coffees used in this blend are naturally processed which means that the coffee beans are dried with the cherry, resulting in complex, fruity and sweet flavours.

Roasted dark to bring out flavours of dark chocolate and fruit jam, this blend's heavy cocoa body leaves a smooth lingering aftertaste.

Our roasting team recommends the Dhak Blend for espresso-based drinks as well as manual brews such as the Moka Pot and the French Press.

products.title: Dhak Blend
products.body_html:
Named after one of our favourite spring blossoms, the Dhak blend is roasted dark to bring out deep flavours of dark chocolate and fruit jam. Its heavy cocoa body leaves a smooth lingering aftertaste and makes for a bold, well-rounded cup of coffee.

products.title: Riverdale Estate – Fruit Punch
products.body_html:
Producer Series ’25 opens with a welcome return from Prakashan Balaraman of Riverdale, a pioneer pushing boundaries through experiments with fruit fermentation and rare varietals. 

For this special lot, Prakashan went a step further, using a blend of tropical fruits during fermentation instead of just one. Ripe cherries were handpicked and triple-washed to remove any floaters before fermentation began. During the first stage, tropical fruits were added in just the right amount to prolong fermentation with natural sugars. Next, in purpose-built tanks, CO₂ was used to flush out oxygen, creating a low-oxygen environment that extended fermentation even further and deepened complexity. After slow drying on raised beds, the coffee was allowed to rest for six weeks for the flavours to stabilise. 

Choosing a light roast profile, our head roaster Shreyas helped shape a cup that opens with the aroma of rich tropical fruits. Bright notes of peach and strawberry follow, layered with hints of red grape and tangerine. A juicy mouthfeel carries through to a clean, lingering mango finish—all coming together to deliver the fruit-forward character that inspired the name, Fruit Punch. 

We recommend brewing this expressive coffee black, as a Pour Over, or using an AeroPress.

Recommended Resting Period: 18 Days

Note: This coffee pack is a special release with limited availability and, therefore, cannot be included in subscription.

products.title: Kerehaklu Estate - Peaberries
products.body_html:
This special two-pack(125 gms each), crafted in partnership with Kerehaklu Estate, features our favourite mutation, a Peaberry. Coffee cherries usually hold two seeds but about 5-10% of the time, just one seed grows inside the cherry. This is a Peaberry. Small, round, and denser than regular coffee beans, it boasts a unique flavour profile, with a deeper sweetness and a brighter acidity. 

Carefully isolated by Pranoy, Ajoy, and team at the farm, the Peaberries that lent to the creation of this pack were processed in two distinct ways: - 

Washed (Aerobic Sequential)  

This lot underwent a sequential aerobic fermentation, where Peaberries were submerged in water for an extended period, creating an oxygen-rich environment that brought out complexity, clarity, and bright acidity.  

Roasted light, these make for a cup with the aroma of brown sugar and citrus, and a juicy mouthfeel that opens into notes of mosambi, toffee, and green grape. The aftertaste is sweet and reminds of ripe mosambis.  

Natural (Anoxic) 

Fermented in an oxygen-free environment, the coffee cherries in this lot experienced a slower, more complex fermentation, since the microbes had more time to break down the sugars present, and produce a wider range of aromatic compounds. The result is a rich, fruity flavour profile with a deep body and balance.  

Roasted light, these make for a cup with the aroma of red grape and dark cherries, and a creamy mouthfeel revealing notes of orange, red grape, and red apple. Punctuating each sip is a lingering aftertaste of red apple.   

We recommend brewing these coffees black as a Pour Over or using an AeroPress.

Recommended Resting Period: 15 Days

Note: This coffee pack is a special release with limited availability and, therefore, cannot be included in our Mixed Bag subscription.

products.title: MSP Micro Lot Blend
products.body_html:
A melting pot of micro-climates where some of India’s finest coffee has thrived since 1920, MSP Coffee is a group of seven estates in Yercaud, including the three that lend to this blend. 

From achieving a surprisingly sweet cup after fermenting coffee with a local variety of bitter lemons to seeing the tail end of a 1000-hour ferment, the group exemplifies how curiosity lies at the heart of their work. The micro lots we picked for this blend come from Bison Valley Estate, Stanmore Estate, and Orchardale Estate and bear this very spirit. 

The first lot was washed and fermented with melon extract, with the processing imparting a unique sweetness. The second underwent triple fermentation: first as whole cherries, then after depulping, and finally after washing. This process uniquely combined quick dry fermentation and long anaerobic fermentation with watermelon, developing complexity. The third coffee was processed using the natural method, with cherries dried intact, allowing the fruit to shape its character. 

Roasted medium, the blend has a fruity and punchy flavour profile with notes of cherry, dark chocolate, and wild berry, followed by a rich, lingering aftertaste of chocolate. 

This blend works well black as well as with milk and lends itself nicely to most brewing methods including espresso, Pour Over, Moka Pot, French Press, AeroPress, and Cold Brew.

Recommended Resting Period: 7 Days

products.title: Attikan Estate
products.body_html:
Sweet with fruity overtones and balanced acidity, Attikan Estate is the darkest of our standard medium roasts and is perfect to brew an espresso with. It boasts of a bold and fruity profile, rounded off with a hint of nuttiness.

products.title: Riverdale Estate - White Rose
products.body_html:
Fermented with rose petals, this layered light roast perfectly embodies why Riverdale Estate is a pioneer in experimental processing.  

Only the ripest cherries, hand-picked from the higher-altitude blocks of the farm, where the fruit matures slowly and develops an enhanced sweetness, were used. Once harvested, the cherries underwent a triple wash with natural spring water to remove impurities, followed by a floating process to eliminate underdeveloped beans.  

During fermentation, rose petals were introduced, setting up the stage for complexity in the cup. After fermentation, the cherries were slow-dried on raised beds for up to 30 days, allowing for even drying. Finally, the coffee was hulled at the estate’s dry mill, where any defective beans were eliminated before being sent to our roastery.  

In the cup, you’ll experience bright notes of blood orange, passion fruit, and pomegranate, complemented by a creamy mouthfeel and a lingering sweetness.  

We recommend brewing it black using an AeroPress or as a Pour Over.

Note: This coffee is a special release with limited availability and, therefore, cannot be included in our Mixed Bag subscription.

products.title: Raxidi Estate - Natural
products.body_html:
Our partnership with Raxidi Estate, a coffee farm run by three generations of the Lobo family since the 1950s, begins with an experimental anaerobic natural. 

To shape this micro lot into a cup with remarkable depth, handpicked coffee cherries were washed and placed in stainless steel containers, where they underwent a 20-hour anaerobic fermentation. Once fermented, the cherries were carefully dried on raised beds for 21 days, with temperature and humidity carefully monitored. 

Roasted light, the resulting brew opens with the aroma of prunes and black raisin, and notes of plum, raspberry, and mosambi. The mouthfeel is smooth and syrupy with a medium body, and finishing each sip is the sweet aftertaste of plum.  

Best enjoyed black, we recommend brewing this coffee using an AeroPress, or as a Pour Over.

products.title: Wine Barrel Aged Coffee
products.body_html:
Meet our three-pack of wine barrel aged coffees, beautifully merging the world of fine wine and specialty coffee.  

Green coffee beans sourced from Baarbara Estate were aged for seven weeks in Fratelli wine barrels that had previously held three of their exceptional wines. The barrels were rotated every 5 days to ensure even infusion, and samples were drawn regularly to track the beans’ flavour development. After ageing, the beans rested for 10-15 days in our warehouses and were then roasted to a medium profile.  

From this process, three distinct, layered, and comforting coffees have emerged. Named after the wines previously stored in the barrels used during processing, the coffees in this selection are:  

  • MS Late Harvest treats you to notes of black cherry, prune, and red wine. 
  • Sette Collection brews cups with notes of red grape, orange, and walnut. 
  • J'Noon White tastes of sparkling wine, stone fruits, and raspberry. 

We recommend brewing this selection black.  

Note: The wine-like tasting notes in these coffees are a result of their unique processing. All offerings in this pack are non-alcoholic.

products.title: Silver Oak 250g + Channi
products.body_html:
